<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="843" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.032/3.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Message of President <persName type="from">Diaz</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Mexican
                                    Congress</gloss> of April 1, 1911.</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-01">April 1, 1911</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>The Government has given special attention and granted certain privileges
                            to work on the Colorado River dikes, which is being done m Baja
                            California territory by an authorized Mexican company.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>